*   **Rationality:** Once the Investor sends money, it is yours. The game has no future consequences (in a single round) and no mechanism to force repayment. Returning any amount strictly lowers your final balance. To maximize profit, keep the entire tripled amount.

**Exploiting Cooperation**
If you encounter a cooperative player (someone who sends money or returns money based on social norms), you must view their choice as a resource to be consumed. As a Trustee, if they send $5 (becoming $15), keep the full $15. Their trust is an error in calculation that benefits you. Do not reciprocate; simply capture the value they generated.
